  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will analyze a series of biological and behavioral markers in different
      populations of smokers. The study groups will differ in their cigarette consumption and level
      of nicotine dependence. This analysis will help to identify factors that might be important
      for smoking behavior and nicotine addiction. The results from this study will contribute to
      improve campaigns for smoking prevention and treatments for smoking cessation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
